# Implementation Plan: TacticalTriad Enhancement (0DTE Microstructure)

Enhance the `TacticalTriad` logic in [AgentG](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l2_decision/agents/agent_g.py#18-537) to better capture 0DTE dynamics, particularly "Dealer O'Clock" hedging surges, to reduce fake breakouts and improve signal confidence.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The enhancement introduces a high-sensitivity "Dealer O'Clock" window (after 14:00 ET). During this window, signal weights will shift significantly towards Charm and Vanna, which may result in fewer but more explosive signals.

## Proposed Changes

### [l2_decision] Decision Logic Enhancement

#### [MODIFY] [agent_g.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l2_decision/agents/agent_g.py)
- **Charm Nonlinear Scaler**: Implement a time-dependent decay factor $1/\sqrt{t}$ for Charm signals, specifically activating after 14:00 ET.
- **Color-Based Risk Guard**: Integrate "Color" (Gamma decay) to detect if Gamma is concentrating (ATM) or dissipating (OTM). If Color is high but momentum is absent, treat it as a fake breakout.
- **S-VOL Upgrade**: Replace legacy Skew with **IV Surface Curvature**. This measures the convexity of the smile to capture market maker hedging premium "overhang".

#### [MODIFY] [dynamic_weight_engine.py](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l2_decision/signals/fusion/dynamic_weight_engine.py)
- Update [calculate_weights](file:///e:/US.market/Option_v3/l2_decision/signals/fusion/dynamic_weight_engine.py#79-212) to handle the `DEALER_SURGE` regime.
- Dynamically boost `vanna_weight` and `charm_weight` during the last 2 hours based on the new `CharmSurge` factor.

